id: pm-d4bo
title: pm claim --if-available (skip when held) — reduce 533 ownership_conflict events
description: "Telemetry: ownership_conflict fires 533 times in 30 days. Agents commonly want \"claim if free, otherwise move on\".\n\nProposed flag: `--if-available` for pm claim. When set, claim returns ok:true with `{claimed: false, held_by: <agent>, expires_at: ...}` instead of erroring on conflict. The current --force flag remains for steal semantics.\n\nAcceptance: tests cover claim/skip/steal trichotomy; MCP pm_claim documented with the new flag."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,claim,locks,pm-cli,telemetry
created_at: "2026-05-17T05:46:58.443Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:15:42.023Z"
deadline: "2026-05-27T05:46:58.443Z"
author: claude-code-agent
resolution: "Implemented pm-d4bo: pm claim --if-available flag skips silently with skipped:true when item is held by another author. Also added claim_takeover:<prev>-><new> warning on default (non-flag) takeovers. Tests added. Targets 533 ownership_conflict events/30d."
expected_result: "Expected result: closure includes explicit resolution metadata and verifiable delivery evidence."
actual_result: "Actual result: Implemented pm-d4bo: pm claim --if-available flag skips silently with skipped:true when item is held by another author. Also added claim_takeover:<prev>-><new> warning on default (non-flag) takeovers. Tests added. Targets 533 ownership_conflict events/30d."
close_reason: "Implemented pm-d4bo: pm claim --if-available flag skips silently with skipped:true when item is held by another author. Also added claim_takeover:<prev>-><new> warning on default (non-flag) takeovers. Tests added. Targets 533 ownership_conflict events/30d."
